Students, Staff, and Parents, school begins tomorrow at 8:30am. I encourage you to sign in early, to ensure you are connected and there are no technical issues.

Please remember, our meal distribution begins tomorrow from 10:30am- 12:00pm @ Madison High School.

Finally, a big shout out to our Staff, Teachers, Principals, and Central office personnel, they have worked so hard this summer in trying to get virtually ready for this school year.

Students, remember to work hard in whatever setting you are in, it will pay great dividends in your future.

As always,

Stay Safe,

Good Evening Families,
We want to let you know that we will begin serving meals again on Tuesday September 8th, from 10:30 AM to 12 PM at Madison High School.

We will be serving meals on Thursday September 10th at Madison High School from 10:30 AM to 12 PM

Beginning September 14th, 2020 we will be serving meals every Monday and Thursday from 10:30AM to 12 PM.

Beginning September 10th, 2020 our FARMERS to FAMILIES fresh Produce begins once a week.

Every child qualifies up to the age of 26 for students with disabilities, or 19 years of age for regular education students. We want to spread the word to as many families as possible.

Stay Safe,
Mr. Abdulahad
